Vice President Kamala Harris spoke to President Isaac Herzog of Israel during her flight to Washington, D.C. from Dubai, where she had discussions with Arab leaders regarding the Israel-Hamas conflict. Harris expressed strong U.S. support for Israel's right to self-defense and they discussed the latest developments in Gaza. They also talked about the situation in the West Bank and expressed concerns about steps that could escalate tensions, such as extremist settler violence. Harris emphasized the importance of planning for the aftermath of the fighting in Gaza and reaffirmed the U.S.' commitment to a two-state solution. To follow up on these discussions, her National Security Advisor, Dr. Phil Gordon, will be traveling to Israel and the West Bank for further talks.